@startuml validation-enforcement
' Where each validation rule with a stated enforcement point is enforced: an apply-time CEL gate that rejects before storage, then a reconcile-time gate that surfaces violations as status on stored objects.
' Source of truth: docs/src/resources/validation-and-defaulting.md
!include _style.puml

skinparam ConditionEndStyle hline
skinparam ActivityDiamondFontSize 11
skinparam ActivityFontSize 12
skinparam ArrowFontSize 10
skinparam wrapWidth 150
skinparam nodesep 12

|$agentBg|Developer|
|$ctrlBg|apiserver / CEL|
|$storeBg|etcd|
|$ctrlBg|Reconciler|
|$gwBg|status|

|Developer|
start
:kubectl apply;

|$ctrlBg|apiserver / CEL|
if (CRD CEL gate\n**16 17 21 25 27**) then (violates)
  |$agentBg|Developer|
  :**rejected**\nbefore storage; <<#FFCDD2>>
  stop
else (passes)
endif

|$storeBg|etcd|
:object stored;

|$ctrlBg|Reconciler|
:reconciler reads\nthe stored object;

switch (reconcile-time gate)
case (resolution\nor validity)
  |$gwBg|status|
  :**Ready=False**\nreason per rule (see table)\n**1 11 12 13 14 15 18**\n**19 22 23 25 27 28**; <<#FFCDD2>>
  stop
case (class\nmismatch)
  |$gwBg|status|
  :**phase=Degraded**\n+ preDegradedPhase\non an **Agent**\n**2 3 4 5 24 26 29**; <<#FFE0B2>>
  stop
case (class\nmismatch)
  |$gwBg|status|
  :**phase=Failed**\nno Degraded phase\non an **AgentTask**\n**2 3 4 5 24**; <<#FFCDD2>>
  stop
case (advisory)
  |$gwBg|status|
  :**Warning event**\nReady unaffected\n**20**; <<#FFF8DC>>
  stop
endswitch

legend bottom
  Every arm below is a violation. A rule that passes both gates leaves **Ready=True**.
  ====
  **Scope.** This draws the rules that reject or degrade. Two categories are not drawn
  as arms. The provider-access rules (3, 4, 5) join rule 2 in the ClassConstraintViolation
  row of the table below. The cap rules (6, 7, 8, 9, 10) do not reject at all: they
  **clamp** the effective value to the class maximum at reconcile time, so a workload that
  asks for more silently gets the cap rather than an error.
  ====
  **Why the reconcile-time rules cannot be CEL.** Three structural reasons:
  the rule **spans two resources** and CEL on an Agent cannot read AgentClass (24, 26);
  it needs **metadata.namespace**, which CRD validation cannot reach at any scope,
  only metadata.name and metadata.generateName (15, 28);
  or it must surface on **pre-existing objects** as recoverable status rather than a
  blocked write (29). Agentry runs no admission webhook server, so there is no third place.
  ====
  |= rule |= reason |= rule |= reason |
  | 15 | InvalidPath / PathConflict | 2, 3, 4, 5 | ClassConstraintViolation |
  | 19 | InvalidCIDR | 24 | PersistenceNotAllowed |
  | 22 | InvalidCallbackUrl | 26 | HibernationNotAllowed |
  | 23 | ImagePullSecretMissing | 29 | HibernationRequiresPersistence |
  | 25 | CallbackAuthMissing / CallbackAuthInvalid | 20 | FQDNPolicyUnsupported |
  | 27 | ExistingClaimNotFound | 14 | AgentServiceDisabled |
  | 28 | SystemNamespaceForbidden | 18 | InvalidDegradeTarget |
  | 1, 11, 12, 13 | Ready=False (reference resolution) | 6-10 | clamped, no reject |
endlegend

@enduml
